==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[tadde]]'', ''[[tode]]'', from Old English ''[[tadige|tādige]]''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-toad.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''toad''' (''plural'' '''toads''')

# an [[amphibian]] similar to a [[frog]] with bigger back legs and more [[ragged]] skin
# very unpleasant man

